<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="199" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="199">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="199">
In the original description, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4039/entm114122fv" author="Schmid, F" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de la Societe Entomologique du Canada" pageId="0" pageNumber="199" pagination="1 - 126" refId="B14" refString="Schmid, F, 1982. La famille des xiphocentronides (Trichoptera: Annulipalpia). Memoires de la Societe Entomologique du Canada 121: 1 - 126, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4039/entm114122fv" title="La famille des xiphocentronides (Trichoptera: Annulipalpia)." url="https://doi.org/10.4039/entm114122fv" volume="121" year="1982">Schmid (1982)</bibRefCitation>
did not provide the full depiction of the dorsal and ventral view of the male genitalia of this species. Therefore, some characters cannot be observed, such as the shape of the anterior margin of the tergum IX in dorsal view and the basal crenulate area of the inferior appendage in ventral view. The holotype is fixed in a permanent slide in dorso-lateral view. To avoid damaging it, we illustrated another identified specimen (from Oaxaca) and analyzed the holotype with material from the same province of the holotype (Veracruz) and other regions of Mexico.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
